gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 110, Thunder 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Rockets defeated the Thunder, 110-101. Dillon Brooks led the way with 23 points, four rebounds, and two assists for the Rockets, while Aaron Holiday added a season-high 22 points (6-7 3PM), six rebounds, and four assists in the victory. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander tallied 33 points, six assists, and three rebounds for the Thunder in the loss. The Rockets improve to 9-9 in the regular season, while the Thunder fall to 13-7.
